ation:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">interview</a></u> with my partne=
r <b>Matt Belloni</b>, NBCU Media Group chairman <b>Mark Lazarus</b> noted =
that Peacock had successfully used its NFL wild card game to <i>introduce <=
/i>new subscribers to the service, many of whom stayed to watch non-sports =
content. In fact, he told Matt, nine of the 10 hours that football fans wou=
ld watch over the next month had <i>nothing</i> to do with football. NBC of=
ficials recently said that 70 percent of their new NFL
sign-ups were still Peacock subscribers after two months.</li><br/><li><i>V=
enu on the menu?</i>: Puck=E2=80=99s resident legal expert <b>Eriq Gardner =
</b>spent last week hunkered down in a New York courtroom watching FuboTV=
=E2=80=99s case against Venu (n=C3=A9 Spulu), the sports streaming service =
coming from ESPN, Fox, and Warner Bros. Discovery. And while you have to wa=
it until tomorrow to read Eriq=E2=80=99s excellent analysis in Puck=E2=80=
=99s What I=E2=80=99m Hearing+ private email, I couldn=E2=80=99t help askin=
g him for a quick summary. Here=E2=80=99s a teaser=E2=80=A6<br/><br/>=E2=80=
=9CFrom the several days of testimony I witnessed, filled with executives, =
consultants, and economists making their case, it feels like a preliminary =
injunction might just be on the table,=E2=80=9D Eriq told me. =E2=80=9CMy a=
ssessment might startle those accustomed to decades of largely unchecked co=
nsolidation and vertical integration in entertainment. Yet, in these days o=
f colossal sports rights valuations, I sense that U.S. District Court Judge=
 <b>Margaret
Garnett </b>grasps, and is concerned by, the extraordinary influence potent=
ially wielded by an alliance of the sector=E2=80=99s behemoths.=E2=80=9D<br=
/><br/>Two weeks ago, I <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpb=
F9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dSU1lkWHRKSHRMUXo0cENlRGxsVT0iLCJocmVmIjoi=
